Key Match Events: England thrashed India by 10 wickets and won the match in just 16 overs
Buttler hit 80 runs and Hales hit 86 runs
Pre-Game Insights: England is looking forward to winning the final against Pakistan
Pakistan suffered a lot of defeats but they made their comeback and reached to finals
Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan smashed key half-centuries which helped Pakistan to reach in ICC T20 World Cup final
Miscellaneous Highlights: The ICC T20 World Cup final will be played between Pakistan and England on 13 November 2022
Pakistan has the second-finest Powerplay economy rate (6.19) and an average of (18.58)
Others: The match officials announced for the title clash between England and Pakistan include umpires Marais Erasmus and Kumar Dharmasena, TV umpire Chris Gaffaney, and fourth umpire Paul Reiffel
